Date:  0/0/1949
Source:  Dictionary of the Underworld
Author:  PARTRIDGE
Vol / Page:  368
Edition:  1961
Quote:  (Usually pl.: Johns.) A policeman, a detective if in uniform: British tramps' c. (and Australian s.) of C. 20: Hugh Milner, letter of April 22, 1935; 1941, Val Davis, Phenomena in Crime. Also American c. of ca. 1925-45 (then s.): Raymond Chandler, Farewell, My Lovely, 1940: prob. of independent origin (John Law). Also - prob. ex England - South African, since ca. 1910: J.B. Fisher, letter of May 22, 1946.
